cific" value="false" checked></td><td class="row1"><em>Upload to the Site</em>: the image will be used for the site (search, changes, etc.) and for pages that don't override it with their own upload. If you want your entire AniAniWeb to use this image, this should be your choice.</td></tr><tr><td class="row2" align=right valign=top><input type="radio" name="specific" value="true"></td><td class="row2"><em>Upload to this Page</em>: the image will be used for this page and all pages below it in the <a class="internal" href="<?toSiteMap?>">page hierarchy</a>. If you want this section of your AniAniWeb to use this image (different from the rest of the site), this should be your choice.</td></tr><tr><td class="header" colspan=2><b>Image File</b> (<tt>.gif</tt> or <tt>.jpg</tt> or <tt>.png</tt>)</td></tr><tr><td class="row1">Choose:&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td class="row1"><input type="file" name="filestuff"></td></tr><tr><td class="header" colspan=2><input type="submit" value="upload"></td></tr></table></form><h3>Style Sheet</h3><p>The cascading style sheet (CSS) determines the style (or looks) of your site. AniAniWeb makes extensive use of style sheets, so you will be able to customize the look of your site (or a section of your site) by simply changing colors, fonts, etc. in style sheets. The form below will upload a new style sheet. To delete a style sheet, go to <a class="internal" href="<?toUpload?>">uploads</a> and delete the corresponding file (<tt>style.css</tt>).</p><form action="<?toAttachCSS?>"><input type="hidden" name="site" value="true"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=2><tr><td class="header"><b>Upload Style Sheet to the Site</b></td></tr><tr><td class="row1">This style sheet will be the style sheet for the site (search, changes, etc.) and for pages that don't have their own style sheet. If you want your entire AniAniWeb to use only one style sheet, this should be your choice.</td></tr><tr><td class="row2"><textarea name="text" rows=20 cols